cs.CR, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.AI 

The paper discusses cybersecurity and safety monitoring for embedded cyber-physical systems, which involves aspects of computer security (cs.CR), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), software engineering (cs.SE), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on monitoring and mitigating attacks suggests a strong emphasis on security (cs.CR), while the application to flight control systems implies a connection to robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY). The use of software, firmware, and hardware also suggests a connection to software engineering (cs.SE), while the real-time nature of the monitors and the use of adaptable security suggest a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
